The DA’s John Steenhuisen. JOHANNESBURG - DA leader John Steenhuisen has confirmed the party is going to court to challenge President Cyril Ramaphosa's announcement that all public schools will be shut for a month from next Monday. SUMMARY: Ramaphosa's speech on schools closing, corruption The government had faced growing calls to make that decision from unions that said keeping schools open during the peak of the COVID-19 pandemic put the lives of pupils and teachers at risk. The DA says the president has given in to unions who do not have the best interests of learners at heart. DA leader, John Steenhuisen says that his party will be approaching the court to challenge the decision by President Ramaphosa to close schools. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/qtInyrsdAl